body_html:
With @Gubarev 's commit, it looks like we now build properly in Sierra. But, I get a weird runtime error now when I try to run the benchmark or the simple app in the simulator (I'm assuming the camera app is failing because it can't get camera input in the simulator). Benchmark crashes with this output:

I tensorflow/tensorflow/contrib/ios_examples/benchmark/BenchmarkViewController.mm:198] Session created.
I tensorflow/tensorflow/contrib/ios_examples/benchmark/BenchmarkViewController.mm:201] Graph created.
I tensorflow/tensorflow/contrib/ios_examples/benchmark/BenchmarkViewController.mm:207] Creating session.
I tensorflow/core/util/stat_summarizer.cc:33] StatSummarizer found 370 nodes
F tensorflow/tensorflow/contrib/ios_examples/benchmark/../../../../tensorflow/core/lib/core/refcount.h:79] Check failed: ref_.load() == 0 (1 vs. 0)
(lldb)

This is on latest master and I made sure to re-run tensorflow/contrib/makefile/download_dependencies.sh

Is this happening for anyone else?

body:
With @Gubarev 's commit, it looks like we now build properly in Sierra.  But, I get a weird runtime error now when I try to run the benchmark or the simple app in the simulator (I'm assuming the camera app is failing because it can't get camera input in the simulator).  Benchmark crashes with this output:

```
I tensorflow/tensorflow/contrib/ios_examples/benchmark/BenchmarkViewController.mm:198] Session created.
I tensorflow/tensorflow/contrib/ios_examples/benchmark/BenchmarkViewController.mm:201] Graph created.
I tensorflow/tensorflow/contrib/ios_examples/benchmark/BenchmarkViewController.mm:207] Creating session.
I tensorflow/core/util/stat_summarizer.cc:33] StatSummarizer found 370 nodes
F tensorflow/tensorflow/contrib/ios_examples/benchmark/../../../../tensorflow/core/lib/core/refcount.h:79] Check failed: ref_.load() == 0 (1 vs. 0)
(lldb) 
```

This is on latest master and I made sure to re-run `tensorflow/contrib/makefile/download_dependencies.sh`

Is this happening for anyone else?
